und" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://ember-climate.org/insights/research/global-electricity-review-2024/">Ember</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> The US is <a href="https://x.com/johnrhanger/status/1795765542004871293">not lagging</a> here. In March, <a href="https://www.eia.gov/electricity/monthly/epm_table_grapher.php?t=table_1_01">according to the EIA</a> , solar and wind generated 21.2% of US electricity, renewables generated 29.9%, and renewables and nuclear combined generated 49.4%.</p><p> Although Biden&#39;s climate policies are great, they haven&#39;t had much chance to take effect yet, and many countries don&#39;t have similar policies in place. The rapid shift toward renewables is being driven by technological improvements that make renewable energy — especially <a href="https://x.com/johnrhanger/status/1773314691185463622">solar and batteries</a> — really cheap.</p><p> We can see this just by observing the actions of countries and states that care much much more about economic growth than about climate change.</p><p> India, despite suffering intense heat waves, makes growth its overriding priority and <a href="https://www.spglobal.com/commodityinsights/en/market-insights/latest-news/energy-transition/112923-cop28-india-doubles-down-on-right-to-increase-climate-emissions">reserves the right</a> to continue using fossil fuels on the grounds that Western countries industrialized using fossil fuels in their day.然而，在今年的第一季度，自去年以来，在印度的太阳能装置<a href="https://x.com/sarthakgh/status/1794351907659829758">增加</a>了<em><a href="https://x.com/sarthakgh/status/1794351907659829758">六倍以上</a></em>。</p><p> And Texas, a deeply conservative state that&#39;s also the center of America&#39;s fossil fuel industry, is outpacing California and everybody else in terms of building solar: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faea67207-a32b-4c83-be9a-3be470028a57_1300x902.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faea67207-a32b-4c83-be9a-3be470028a57_1300x902.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faea67207-a32b-4c83-be9a-3be470028a57_1300x902.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faea67207-a32b-4c83-be9a-3be470028a57_1300x902.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faea67207-a32b-4c83-be9a-3be470028a57_1300x902.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faea67207-a32b-4c83-be9a-3be470028a57_1300x902.jpeg" width="704" height="488.4676923076923" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/aea67207-a32b-4c83-be9a-3be470028a57_1300x902.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:902,&quot;width&quot;:1300,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:704,&quot;bytes&quot;:112257,&quot;alt&